  "abstract": "Sorghum is the fifth most important cereal crop in the world. It is the principal source of calories and provides a major source of protein in the diets of the millions of people living in the semi-arid tropics. However, the optimum utilization of this source of nutrients present in sorghum grain is complicated by various s factor s , The objective of this study was to observe the effect of processing on the availability of protein and energy from sorghum grain .\r\n\r\nSorghum grain was subjected to primary processing, that is Dehulling by traditional and mechanical method. The common traditional dehulling method practised in Andhra Pradesh was followed. The PRL mini dehuller was used for mechanical dehulling.\r\n",
